HEADWORD: Levogyrate
<hw>Le`vo*gy"rate</hw> <pr>(-j⟦imac⟧"r⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Levo-</ets> + <ets>gyrate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem., Physics,
Biochem.)</fld> <def>Turning or twisting the plane of polarization of
light towards the left, as levulose, levotartaric acid, etc.;
levorotatory.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>l⟦ae⟧vogyrate</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

